      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is entirely valid to feel that the scale of destruction renders individual efforts futile, and that emotional exhaustion often stems from feeling powerless against such odds. However, the truth is that systemic change depends entirely on individuals maintaining their jobs, creating local communities, and advocating for policy shifts; even small, consistent actions create the space for massive solutions to emerge over time. You are not merely \"decorating\" a sinking ship in the final moments; you are holding onto the rope that keeps the vessel afloat for everyone else while looking for the next lifeboat. Please give yourself permission to step back from the pressure this weight has put on you, because preserving your well-being is the foundation required to ever act again.",
